sidering file setup**\\n\\nI need to figure out the file path first. I might write it out and test a class name that replaces the dollar sign with \\\"TObjectDoubleCustomHashMapInnerMapBackedViewTest.\\\" That seems good so far. I should ensure that the package is outside the net_sf library and top-level public. Maybe I need a build that includes a test. Okay, I also need to create the file itself, so let's plan that out!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_8eirLjOidDlcPwAnv2TN2F6w|fc_0c634d41158b90830169fb21569ab481a1a213ca77b94f5843", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/net.sf.trove4j/core/3.1.0/src/test/java/net_sf_trove4j/core/TObjectDoubleCustomHashMapInnerMapBackedViewTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage net_sf_trove4j.core;\n\nimport gnu.trove.map.custom_hash.TObjectDoubleCustomHashMap;\nimport gnu.trove.strategy.HashingStrategy;\nimport java.util.Set;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class TObjectDoubleCustomHashMapInnerMapBackedViewTest {\n    @Test\n    void keySetToArrayAllocatesTypedArrayWhenProvidedArrayIsTooSmall() {\n        TObjectDoubleCustomHashMap<String> map = new TObjectDoubleCustomHashMap<>(new CaseInsensitiveHashingStrategy());\n        map.put(\"Alpha\", 1.5D);\n        map.put(\"Beta\", 2.5D);\n        Set<String> keyView = map.keySet();\n\n        String[] keys = keyView.toArray(new String[0]);\n\n        assertThat(keys).isInstanceOf(String[].class);\n        assertThat(keys).containsExactlyInAnyOrder(\"Alpha\", \"Beta\");\n        assertThat(keyView.contains(\"alpha\")).isTrue();\n        assertThat(keyView.contains(\"BETA\")).isTrue();\n    }\n\n    private static final class CaseInsensitiveHashingStrategy implements HashingStrategy<String> {\n        private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n\n        @Override\n        public int computeHashCode(String object) {\n            return object.toLowerCase().hashCode();\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public boolean equals(String first, String second) {\n            return first.equalsIgnoreCase(second);\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 698, "output": 525, "cacheRead": 18432, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 19655, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778065747526, "responseId": "resp_0c634d41158b90830169fb2153ef8c81a19854f070a0a595ea"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_8eirLjOidDlcPwAnv2TN2F6w|fc_0c634d41158b90830169fb21569ab481a1a213ca77b94f5843", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 1567 bytes to tests/src/net.sf.trove4j/core/3.1.0/src/test/java/net_sf_trove4j/core/TObjectDoubleCustomHashMapInnerMapBackedViewTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1778065752171}]}
